The Inkopolitian State wrote:In this timeline, the United Kingdom proposed a referendum in 1949 to transform the country into a republic. This referendum succeeded, and the United Kingdom was renamed to the United Republic. This referendum also saw the abolition of the House of Lords and the installation of walfare within Great Britain.

Overview of Inkopolitia wrote:The Great Dying

Thanks to a disease, Inklings and Octolings alike faced a catastrophe of unknown proportions. The disease spread rapidly and killed rapidly. The reason why it spread so rapidly was because of the poor sanization in in urban centers. This disease lasted from 1600 to 1604. The disease, originating in Takodisian territories and killing 56% of the Octoling population, soon spread to Inklings, killing 49% of the Inkling population. This initiated massive changes in Inkceph society. Most Anthropologists believe that if the plague -as terrible as it was- didn't happen, the uncontrolled population of Inkcephs would be devastating to modern-day Inkopolitia, as the country would likely suffer from problems related to overpopulation.

I have learned about a disease that wiped a good percentage of them, and given the death rates and all, we Valentians can relate, yo... Disease, war, whatever... they have been majorly devastating for all of us, and I'm sad t hear that the 4-year-long disease was... let's just say it's starting to sound like the Inkling version of The Black Plague.

by Khoronzon » Sun Oct 20, 2019 10:23 am

The beginning of Inkceph civilisation was in 213 AD, when a loosely knit island village banded together to form the city-state of Iliania and proceeded to dominate its surrounding territory. This event was known as the State Jump. Other villages tried to emulate this model, creating city-states of their own, which resulted in an approximately 800-year period of constant power struggles between these city-states known as the Centuries of Conflict.

AN: The American Imperial family, the house of Reventlow, is of Russian descent and originates from the house of Romanov. There is also a noticeable lack of women in the family.
